    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static List<String> get(String raw)
        Gets the list of comma-separated arguments in the given string.

        This will handle if the given string is encased in parenthesis, e.g., (arg1, arg2). This does not distinguish between commas inside of quotes or handle escaped commas.

        For example given the following: 

             (arg1, arg2)

        This will return: 

             List[arg1, arg2]

        If only iterating over the args, use iterate(String) instead.

        Parameters:
        raw - Get the args from this string.
        Returns:
        The list of individual (trimmed) arguments.

      • iterate

        public static Iterable<String> iterate(String raw)
        Gets the list of comma-separated arguments in the given string. This should be used when you are only iterating over the args, i.e., not accessing by index.

        This will handle if the given string is encased in parenthesis, e.g., (arg1, arg2). This does not distinguish between commas inside of quotes or handle escaped commas.

        Parameters:
        raw - Get the args from this string.
        Returns:
        An iterable containing the individual (trimmed) arguments).

      • trimParens

        public static String trimParens(String raw)
        Removes the opening and closing parens, only if the first character is a '(' and last character is a ')' (whitespace is trimmed before doing this check). If parens are trimmed then whitespace inside of the parens is trimmed as well.

        For example given the following: 

            (arg1, arg2 )

        This will return: 

             "arg1, arg2"
        Parameters:
        raw - Trim opening and closing parens from this string.
        Returns:
        The string with the opening and closing parens trimmed, or the string unchanged if it is not encased in parens.

      • extract

        public static String extract(String raw)
        Extracts the args inside of a function literal.

        For example given the following: 

             customFunction(arg1, arg2)

        This will return: 

             "arg1, arg2"
        Parameters:
        raw - Extract the args from this function literal.
        Returns:
        The extracted args.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - If encasing parenthesis are not present in the given string.

      • trimQuotesSimple

        public static String trimQuotesSimple(String raw)
        Strips matching, encasing quotes (" or ') from the given string.

        Note that this does not support quote escaping, and it will only strip the quotes if the opening quote is not closed before the end of the string. For example, these will be trimmed: 

             "abc def"
     'abc def'

        however this will not: 

             "abc" + 123 + "abc"
        Parameters:
        raw - Trim the quotes around this string.
        Returns:
        The string with the quotes trimmed, or the same string as given if it does not meet the criteria described above.

      • trimDoubleQuotes

        public static String trimDoubleQuotes(String raw)
        Strips matching double quotes from the given string.

        Note that this does not support quote escaping, and it will only strip the quotes if the opening quote is not closed before the end of the string. For example, this will be trimmed: 

             "abc def"

        however this will not: 

             "abc" + 123 + "abc"
        Parameters:
        raw - Trim the quotes around this string.
        Returns:
        The string with the quotes trimmed, or the same string as given if it does not meet the criteria described above.

        Returns:
        The formatted arguments.
